# Admin UI Enhancements — Usability & System Improvements

You are improving the Admin UI beyond basic requirements to make the system more efficient, intuitive, and scalable.

---

## 1. Improved Criteria Management UX
Enhance usability by:
- Drag-and-drop reordering of criteria/sub-criteria
- Expand/collapse hierarchy view
- Bulk edit for marks
- Duplicate criteria (for new academic year setup)

---

## 2. Smart Defaults & Templates
Add:
- Predefined templates for common criteria structures
- Option to copy previous academic year criteria into new year

Purpose:
- Reduce setup time for admin

---

## 3. Validation & Error Prevention
Implement:
- Real-time validation (marks, required fields)
- Warnings before deleting criteria with dependencies
- Prevent incomplete configurations

---

## 4. Status Indicators
Add:
- Clear labels:
  - Active / Inactive academic year
  - Locked / Unlocked criteria
- Visual indicators for system state

---

## 5. Audit & Change Tracking
Implement:
- Show last modified date/time for:
  - Criteria
  - Marks
- Display "modified by" user

Purpose:
- Transparency and accountability

---

## 6. Search & Filtering
Add:
- Search criteria by name
- Filter users by role/department
- Quick navigation for large datasets

---

## 7. Notifications / Feedback
Add:
- Success/error messages for actions
- Confirmation prompts for critical actions (lock, delete)

---

## 8. Performance & Scalability Considerations
Ensure:
- Efficient rendering of large criteria lists
- Lazy loading or pagination where needed

---

## 9. UI/UX Principles
Follow:
- Minimal clicks to perform actions
- Clear hierarchy visualization
- Consistent layout and spacing
- Avoid clutter (use tables + modals instead of excessive cards)

---

## 10. Future-Ready Design
Prepare UI for:
- Integration with backend APIs
- Role-based access control
- Multi-year data handling

---

## Goal
Make the Admin UI:
- Fast to configure
- Hard to misuse
- Easy to understand
- Scalable for real-world use